'''PJKT Lenz''' (also written '''Projekt: Lenz''' or '''PJKT: Lenz''') is a community film festival in [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat|VRChat]] organized by [[Community:PJKT|Projekt: Community]] (PJKT).<ref name="legends-wiki">[https://vrchat-legends.fandom.com/wiki/Projekt:_Community "Projekt: Community"] on ''VRChat Legends Wiki''. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> The festival showcases short films submitted by VRChat creators and includes programming about filmmaking alongside screenings and ceremony-style sessions.<ref name="legends-wiki"/><ref name="fa-lenz-promo">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/53925448/ "PJKT Lenz 2023 - Promo Poster"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity''. Retrieved July 18, 2026.</ref>

==Overview==

Event publicity has described it as a festival highlighting community-made films, with an open call for submissions ahead of the run.<ref name="fa-lenz-promo"/> Film-festival submissions have also been accepted during broader PJKT Fest sign-up periods in later years.<ref name="fa-2024-signups">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/56443199/ "Projekt: Community Festival 2024 - Sign-Ups Open!"] on ''Fur Affinity'' (community-uploaded event publicity; includes historical dates and links). Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref>

==Format==

Documented editions have used a dedicated festival world for screenings, staff programming, and closing ceremonies.<ref name="fa-lenz-promo"/><ref name="fa-lenz-closing">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/53925881/ "PJKT Lenz 2023 - Summon The Crowds"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity''. Retrieved July 18, 2026.</ref><ref name="fa-lenz-staff">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/53925930/ "PJKT Lenz 2023 - Staff Assembled"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity''. Retrieved July 18, 2026.</ref> Alongside film showings, the program has included talk-oriented sessions about filmmaking.<ref name="legends-wiki"/>

==History==

===2023===

PJKT Lenz 2023 ran from September 29 to October 1, 2023, in a festival world credited to Pesky12.<ref name="fa-lenz-promo"/><ref name="fa-lenz-closing"/> Promotional materials invited film submissions and framed the weekend as a showcase of VRChat community productions.<ref name="fa-lenz-promo"/> Closing ceremonies were led on-stage by festival staff, including Chris Kani.<ref name="fa-lenz-staff"/>

